  <Summary>Immortal Coil is a dark and modern reimagining of Norse mythology infused with cosmic horror, set in a modern world teetering on the edge of oblivion. This ongoing mini-series explores the ancient, forgotten truths behind Ragnarok. The true purpose of Ragnarok was to banish Loki and protect Odin’s family at all costs, but now Loki returns with a vengeance, seeking to unleash Nyarlathotep's apocalyptic power with the aid of his daughter, Hel. As Loki awakens, the series delves into the battle between divine bloodlines and eldritch horrors as Earth becomes the final battleground for the existence of mortals and immortals alike. The opening issues reveal that the Norse gods have secretly survived Ragnarok and made Earth their final home, hidden among humans. With Odin's death at Loki’s hands, Hel awakens to assist her father in unleashing Nyarlathotep's power. Desperate, Odin must awaken his dormant grandchildren—living as humans—to stop Loki before the mortal and Immortal worlds collapse.</Summary>
